  <Name>k__BackingField: Nehemiah
  fancyName: 
  nickname: neh
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Nehemiah\u2019s Grief for the Exiles"
      title: "Nehemiah\u2019s Grief for the Exiles"
      number: 1
      content: '  The words of Nehemiah son of Hacaliah:  Now it happened in the
        month of Chislev, in the twentieth year [of the Persian king], as I was in
        the capitol of Susa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Hanani, one of my brothers, and some men from Judah came; and I asked
        them about the surviving Jews who had escaped and survived the captivity,
        and about Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They said to me, \u201CThe remnant there in the province who survived
        the captivity are in great distress and reproach; the wall of Jerusalem is
        broken down and its [fortified] gates have been burned (destroyed) by fire.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now it came about when I heard these words, I sat down and wept and
        mourned for days; and I was fasting and praying [constantly] before the God
        of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I said, \u201CPlease, O Lord God of heaven, the great and awesome
        God, who keeps the covenant and lovingkindness for those who love Him and
        keep His commandments, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "please let Your ear be attentive and Your eyes open to hear the prayer
        of Your servant which I am praying before You, day and night, on behalf of
        Your servants, the sons (descendants) of Israel (Jacob), confessing the sins
        of the sons of Israel which we have committed against You; I and my father\u2019s
        house have sinned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'We have acted very corruptly against You and have not kept the commandments,
        nor the statutes, nor the ordinances which You commanded Your servant Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Please remember the word which You commanded Your servant Moses,
        saying, \u2018If you are unfaithful and violate your obligations to Me I
        will scatter you [abroad] among the peoples; "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "but if you return to Me and keep My commandments and do them, though
        those of you who have been scattered are in the most remote part of the heavens,
        I will gather them from there and will bring them to the place where I have
        chosen for My Name to dwell.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now they are Your servants and Your people whom You have redeemed
        by Your great power and by Your strong hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Please, O Lord, let Your ear be attentive to the prayer of Your servant
        and the prayer of Your servants who delight to [reverently] fear Your Name
        [Your essence, Your nature, Your attributes, with awe]; and make Your servant
        successful this day and grant him compassion in the sight of this man [the
        king].\u201D  For I was cupbearer to the king [of Persia]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Nehemiah\u2019s Prayer Answered"
      title: "Nehemiah\u2019s Prayer Answered"
      number: 1
      content: '  In the month of Nisan, in the twentieth year of King Artaxerxes,
        when wine was placed before him, I took the wine and gave it to the king.
        Now I had not [previously] been sad in his presence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the king said to me, \u201CWhy do you look sad when you are not
        sick? This is nothing but sadness of heart.\u201D Then I was very frightened, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and I said to the king, \u201CLet the king live forever. Why should
        my face not be sad when the city, the place of my fathers\u2019 tombs, lies
        desolate and its gates have been consumed by fire?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The king said to me, \u201CWhat do you request?\u201D So I prayed
        to the God of heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I said to the king, \u201CIf it pleases the king, and if your servant
        has found favor in your presence, [I ask] that you send me to Judah, to the
        city of my fathers\u2019 tombs, so that I may rebuild it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The king, beside whom the queen was sitting, asked me, \u201CHow
        long will your journey take, and when will you return?\u201D So it pleased
        the king to send me, and I gave him a definite time [for my return]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then I said to the king, \u201CIf it pleases the king, let letters
        be given to me for the governors of the provinces beyond the [Euphrates]
        River, so that they will allow me to pass through until I reach Judah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and a letter to Asaph, the keeper of the king\u2019s forest, so that
        he will give me timber to construct beams for the gates of the fortress which
        is by the temple, and for the city wall and for the house which I will occupy.\u201D
        And the king granted me what I asked, for the good hand of my God was upon
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then I came to the governors of the provinces beyond the [Euphrates]
        River and gave them the king\u2019s letters. Now the king had sent officers
        of the army and horsemen with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Nehemiah Inspects Jerusalem\u2019s Walls"
      title: "Nehemiah Inspects Jerusalem\u2019s Walls"
      number: 10
      content: 'When Sanballat the Horonite and Tobiah the Ammonite official heard
        this, it caused them great displeasure that someone had come to see about
        the welfare and prosperity of the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So I came to Jerusalem and was there for three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then I got up in the night, I and a few men with me. I did not tell
        anyone what my God was putting in my heart to do for Jerusalem, and there
        was no animal with me except the one on which I was riding [so as not to
        attract attention]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So I went out at night by the Valley Gate toward the Dragon\u2019s
        Well and to the Refuse Gate and inspected the walls of Jerusalem which were
        broken down and its gates which were consumed by fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then I passed over to the Fountain Gate and to the King\u2019s Pool,
        but there was no place for the animal that I was riding to pass. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So I went up at night by the ravine [of Kidron] and inspected the
        wall; then I turned back and entered [the city] by the Valley Gate, and returned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The officials did not know where I had gone or what I had done; nor
        had I yet told the Jews, the priests, the nobles, the officials, or the rest
        who did the work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then I said to them, \u201CYou see the bad situation that we are
        in\u2014how Jerusalem is desolate and lies in ruins and its gates have been
        burned with fire. Come, and let us rebuild the wall of Jerusalem, so that
        we will no longer be a disgrace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then I told them how the hand of my God had been favorable to me
        and also about the words that the king had spoken to me. And they said, \u201CLet
        us rise up and build.\u201D So they thoroughly supported the good work.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But when Sanballat the Horonite and Tobiah the Ammonite official
        and Geshem the Arab heard about it, they mocked us and regarded us with contempt
        and said, \u201CWhat is this thing you are doing? Are you rebelling against
        the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "I answered them, \u201CThe God of heaven [has appointed us for His
        purpose and] will give us success; therefore we His servants will arise and
        build, but you have no portion, right, or memorial in Jerusalem.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Builders of the Walls'
      title: Builders of the Walls
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Eliashib the high priest rose up with his brothers the priests
        and built the Sheep Gate. They consecrated it and set up its doors; and they
        consecrated the wall [westward] to the Tower of the Hundred, as far as the
        Tower of Hananel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Next to Eliashib the men of Jericho built, and next to them Zaccur
        the son of Imri built.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now the sons of Hassenaah built the Fish Gate; they laid its beams
        and set up its doors with its bolts and its bars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Next to them Meremoth the son of Uriah, the son of Hakkoz, made repairs.
        Next to him Meshullam the son of Berechiah, the son of Meshezabel, made repairs.
        And next to him Zadok the son of Baana also made repairs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Next to him the men of Tekoa made repairs, but their nobles did not
        support the work of their overseers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Joiada the son of Paseah and Meshullam the son of Besodeiah repaired
        the Old Gate. They laid its beams and set up its doors with its bolts and
        its bars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Next to them Melatiah the Gibeonite and Jadon the Meronothite, the
        men of Gibeon and of Mizpah, made repairs for the official seat (Jerusalem
        residence) of the governor [of the province] beyond the [Euphrates] River. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Next to them Uzziel the son of Harhaiah, one of the goldsmiths, made
        repairs. Next to him Hananiah, one of the perfumers, made repairs, and they
        restored Jerusalem as far as the Broad Wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Next to them Rephaiah the son of Hur, official of half the district
        of Jerusalem, made repairs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Next to them Jedaiah the son of Harumaph made repairs opposite his
        own house. And next to him Hattush the son of Hashabneiah made repairs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Malchijah the son of Harim and Hasshub the son of Pahath-moab repaired
        another section and the Tower of the Furnaces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Next to him Shallum the son of Hallohesh, the official of half the
        district of Jerusalem, made repairs, he and his daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hanun and the inhabitants of Zanoah repaired the Valley Gate. They
        built it and set up its doors with its bolts and its bars, and repaired a
        thousand cubits (1,500 ft.) of the wall as far as the Refuse Gate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Malchijah the son of Rechab, the official of the district of Beth-haccherem
        repaired the Refuse Gate. He rebuilt it and set its doors with its bolts
        and its bars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Shallum the son of Col-hozeh, official of the district of Mizpah
        repaired the Fountain Gate. He rebuilt it and covered it [with a roof], and
        set up its doors with its bolts and its bars, and [he rebuilt] the wall of
        the Pool of Shelah (Siloam) by the King\u2019s Garden as far as the stairs
        that descend [the eastern slope] from [the section of Jerusalem known as]
        the City of David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'After him Nehemiah the son of Azbuk, official of half the district
        of Beth-zur, repaired [the wall] as far as [a point] in front of the tombs
        of David, and as far as the artificial pool and the house of the guards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'After him the Levites carried out repairs under Rehum the son of
        Bani. Next to him Hashabiah, official of half the district of Keilah, carried
        out repairs for his district. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'After him their brothers carried out repairs under Bavvai the son
        of Henadad, official of [the other] half of the district of Keilah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Next to him Ezer the son of Jeshua, the official of Mizpah, repaired
        another section [northward] in front of the ascent to the armory at the Angle
        [in the wall]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After him Baruch son of Zabbai zealously repaired another section
        [toward the hill], from the Angle [in the wall] to the door of the house
        of Eliashib the high priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "After him Meremoth the son of Uriah, the son of Hakkoz, repaired
        another [eastern] section, from the door of Eliashib\u2019s house as far
        as the end of his house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'After him the priests, the men of the [lower Jordan] valley, carried
        out repairs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After them Benjamin and Hasshub made repairs in front of their house.
        After them Azariah the son of Maaseiah, the son of Ananiah, carried out repairs
        beside his own house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'After him Binnui the son of Henadad repaired another section [of
        the wall], from the house of Azariah to the Angle [in the wall] and to the
        corner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Palal the son of Uzai made repairs in front of the Angle [in the
        wall] and the tower projecting from the upper house (palace) of the king,
        which is by the courtyard of the guard. After him Pedaiah the son of Parosh
        made repairs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The temple servants were living in Ophel [the hill south of the temple],
        and they made repairs as far as the front of the Water Gate on the east and
        the projecting tower. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'After them the Tekoites repaired another section in front of the
        great projecting tower and as far as the wall of Ophel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Above the Horse Gate the priests made repairs, each one in front
        of his own house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'After them Zadok the son of Immer carried out repairs in front of
        his house. After him Shemaiah the son of Shecaniah, keeper of the East Gate,
        repaired the wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'After him Hananiah the son of Shelemiah, and Hanun the sixth son
        of Zalaph, repaired another section. After him Meshullam the son of Berechiah
        carried out repairs in front of his own quarters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'After him Malchijah, one of the goldsmiths, carried out repairs as
        far as the house of the temple servants and of the merchants, in front of
        the Inspection Gate and as far as the upper room of the corner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Between the upper room of the corner and the Sheep Gate the goldsmiths
        and merchants carried out repairs.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Work Is Ridiculed'
      title: Work Is Ridiculed
      number: 1
      content: '    But when Sanballat heard that we were rebuilding the wall, he
        became furious, completely enraged, and he ridiculed the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He spoke before his brothers and the army of Samaria, \u201CWhat
        are these feeble Jews doing? Can they restore it for themselves? Can they
        offer sacrifices? Can they finish in a day? Can they revive the stones from
        the heaps of dust and rubbish, even the ones that have been burned?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now Tobiah the Ammonite was beside him, and he said, \u201CEven what
        they are building\u2014if a fox should get up on it, he would break down
        their stone wall.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '[And Nehemiah prayed] Hear, O our God, how we are despised! Return
        their taunts on their own heads. Give them up as prey in a land of captivity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Do not forgive their wrongdoing and do not let their sin be wiped
        out before You, for they have offended the builders [and provoked You].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So we built the wall and the entire wall was joined together to half
        its height, for the people had a heart to work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  But when Sanballat, Tobiah, the Arabs, the Ammonites, and the Ashdodites
        heard that the repair of the walls of Jerusalem went on, and that the breaches
        were being closed, they were very angry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Discouragement Overcome'
      title: Discouragement Overcome
      number: 8
      content: 'They all conspired together to come and to fight against Jerusalem,
        and to cause a disturbance in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But we prayed to our God, and because of them we set up a guard against
        them day and night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then [the leaders of] Judah said,\u201CThe strength of the burden
        bearers is failing,And there is much rubble;We ourselves are unableTo rebuild
        the wall.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Our enemies said, \u201CThey will not know or see us until we are
        among them, kill them and put a stop to the work.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When the Jews who lived near them came, they said to us ten times
        (repeatedly), \u201CFrom every place you turn, they will come up against
        us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So I stationed armed men behind the wall in the lowest places, at
        the open positions [where it was least protected]; and I stationed the people
        in families with their swords, spears, and bows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When I saw their fear, I stood and said to the nobles and officials
        and the rest of the people: \u201CDo not be afraid of them; [confidently]
        remember the Lord who is great and awesome, and [with courage from Him] fight
        for your brothers, your sons, your daughters, your wives, and for your homes.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now when our enemies heard that we knew about their plot against
        us, and that God had frustrated their plan, we all returned to the wall,
        each one to his work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'From that day on, half of my servants carried on the work while the
        other half held the spears, shields, bows, and breastplates; and the captains
        were behind the whole house of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Those who were rebuilding the wall and those who carried burdens
        loaded themselves so that everyone worked with one hand and held a weapon
        with the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Every builder had his sword secured at his side as he built. And
        the one who sounded the trumpet [to summon the troops] stood at my side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I said to the nobles, the officials and the rest of the people, \u201CThe
        work is great and extensive, and we are separated on the wall, far from one
        another. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Wherever you hear the sound of the trumpet, gather to us there. Our
        God will fight for us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So we carried on with the work with half of them holding spears from
        dawn until the stars came out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "At that time I also said to the people, \u201CLet each man with his
        servant spend the night inside Jerusalem so that they may serve as a guard
        for us at night and a laborer during the day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So neither I, my brothers (relatives), my servants, nor the men of
        the guard who followed me, none of us took off our clothes; each took his
        weapon [even] to the water.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Usury Abolished'
      title: Usury Abolished
      number: 1
      content: '  Now there was a great outcry of the [poorer] people and their wives
        against their Jewish brothers [to whom they were deeply in debt]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For there were some who were saying, \u201CWe, along with our sons
        and our daughters, are many; therefore allow us to get grain, so that we
        may eat and survive.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "There were others who were saying, \u201CWe are mortgaging our fields,
        our vineyards, and our houses to buy grain because of the famine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "There were also others who were saying, \u201CWe have borrowed money
        on our fields and vineyards for the [Persian] king\u2019s [heavy] tax. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now our flesh (skin) is the same as that of our brothers (relatives),
        and our children are like their children, yet here we are forcing (selling)
        our sons and our daughters to be slaves; and some of our daughters are forced
        into bondage already, and we are powerless [to redeem them] because our fields
        and vineyards belong to others.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then I was very angry when I heard their outcry and these words [of
        accusation]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I thought it over and then challenged the nobles and the rulers.
        I said to them, \u201CYou are exacting usury (excessive interest) from your
        own brother (relative).\u201D So I held a great assembly to confront them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I said to them, \u201CAccording to our ability we have redeemed (purchased
        back) our Jewish brothers who were sold to the [Gentile] nations; now would
        you even sell your brothers, that they might be sold to us?\u201D Then they
        were silent and could not find a [single] word to say. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So I said, \u201CWhat you are doing is not good. Should you not walk
        in the fear of our God to prevent the taunting by the [pagan] nations, our
        enemies? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And likewise I, my brothers, and my servants are lending them money
        and grain. Please, let us stop [charging] this interest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Please, give back to them this very day their fields, their vineyards,
        their olive groves, and their houses, and also a hundredth part of the money,
        the grain, the new wine, and the oil that you are lending them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then they said, \u201CWe will give it back and not require anything
        from them. We will do exactly as you say.\u201D Then I called the priests
        and took an oath from them that they would act in accordance with this promise. "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Nehemiah\u2019s Example"
      title: "Nehemiah\u2019s Example"
      number: 13
      content: "I also shook out the front of my garment and said, \u201CSo may God
        shake out every man from his house and from his possessions who does not
        keep this promise; like this may he be shaken out and emptied.\u201D And
        all the assembly said, \u201CAmen!\u201D And they praised the Lord. Then
        the people acted in accordance with this promise.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Moreover, from the day that I was appointed to be their governor
        in the land of Judah, from the twentieth year to the thirty-second year of
        King Artaxerxes, for twelve years, neither I nor my relatives have eaten
        the governor\u2019s food allowance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But the former governors who were [in office] before me put heavy
        burdens on the people and took food and wine from them in addition to forty
        shekels of silver [as an excessive monthly salary]; even their servants assumed
        authority over the people. But I did not do so because of the [reverent]
        fear of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I also applied myself to the work on this wall; we did not buy any
        land, and all my servants were gathered together there for the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Moreover, there were at my table a hundred and fifty Jews and officials,
        besides those who came to us from the nations that were around us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now the following were prepared for each day: one ox and six choice
        sheep; also fowls (poultry) were prepared for me; and in intervals of ten
        days all sorts of wine was provided in abundance. Yet for all this, I did
        not demand the governor\u2019s food allowance, because the servitude was
        heavy on this people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Remember me, O my God, for good, according to all I have done for
        this people.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Enemy\u2019s Plot"
      title: "The Enemy\u2019s Plot"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when Sanballat, Tobiah, Geshem the Arab, and the rest of our
        enemies heard that I had rebuilt the wall, and that there was no breach left
        in it, although at that time I had not set up doors in the gates, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Sanballat and Geshem sent word to me, saying, \u201CCome, let us
        meet together at Chephirim in the plain of Ono.\u201D But they were planning
        to harm me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So I sent messengers to them, saying, \u201CI am doing a great work
        and cannot come down. Why should the work stop while I leave to come down
        to [meet with] you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They sent word to me four times in this way, and I answered them
        in the same way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Sanballat sent his servant to me in the same way the fifth time,
        with an open letter in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "In it was written, \u201CIt is reported among the [neighboring] nations,
        and Gashmu is saying that you and the Jews are planning to revolt, and that
        is the reason you are rebuilding the wall. And according to these reports,
        you are to be their king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Also [it is reported that] you have appointed prophets to make a
        proclamation concerning you in Jerusalem, saying, \u2018There is a king in
        Judah!\u2019 And now these things will be reported to the [Persian] king.
        So come now, and let us consult together.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I sent a message to him, saying, \u201CSuch things as you are saying
        have not been done; you are inventing them in your own mind.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For they all wanted to frighten us, thinking, \u201CThey will become
        discouraged with the work and it will not be done.\u201D But now, [O God,]
        strengthen my hands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When I went into the house of Shemaiah the son of Delaiah, the son
        of Mehetabel, who was confined at home, he said, \u201CLet us meet [and take
        refuge] together in the house of God, within the temple, and let us shut
        the doors of the temple, because they are coming to kill you, and they are
        coming to kill you at night.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But I said, \u201CShould a man like me flee [in fear and hide]? Should
        someone like me enter the temple [for sanctuary] to save his life? I will
        not go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then I realized that God had not sent him, but he spoke this prophecy
        against me because Tobiah and Sanballat had hired him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He was hired for this reason, that I would be frightened and do as
        he said and sin, so that they would have [grounds to make] a malicious report
        in order to censure and disgrace me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Wall Is Finished'
      title: The Wall Is Finished
      number: 14
      content: 'Remember, O My God, Tobiah and Sanballat in regard to these actions
        of theirs, and also [remember] the prophetess Noadiah and the rest of the
        prophets who were trying to frighten me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the wall was finished on the twenty-fifth [day] of [the month]
        Elul, in fifty-two days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When all our enemies heard about it, and all the [Gentile] nations
        around us saw it, they lost their confidence; for they recognized that this
        work had been accomplished with the help of our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Moreover, in those days many letters went from the nobles of Judah
        to Tobiah, and Tobiah\u2019s letters came to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For many in Judah were bound by oath to him because he was the son-in-law
        of Shecaniah the son of Arah, and his son Jehohanan had married the daughter
        of Meshullam the son of Berechiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Also, they were speaking about Tobiah\u2019s good deeds in my presence,
        and reporting to him what I said. Then Tobiah sent letters to frighten me."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Census of First Returned Exiles'
      title: Census of First Returned Exiles
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when the wall had been rebuilt and I had set up the doors,
        and the gatekeepers, singers, and Levites had been appointed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I put my brother Hanani, with Hananiah the commander of the fortress,
        in charge of Jerusalem, for Hananiah was a more faithful and God-fearing
        man than many [of the others]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I said to them, \u201CDo not let the gates of Jerusalem be opened
        until the sun is hot; and while the watchmen are still standing guard, have
        them shut and bar the doors. Appoint guards from the residents of Jerusalem,
        each at his post [on the wall], and each in front of his own house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now the city was spacious and large, but there were few people in
        it and the houses had not [yet] been built.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then my God put it into my heart to assemble the nobles, the officials,
        and the people to be registered by genealogy. Then I found the register of
        the genealogy of those who came [from Babylon] first, and I found the following
        record:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'These are the sons (descendants, people) of the province who came
        up from the captivity of the exiles whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon
        had deported [to Babylon]; they returned to Jerusalem and to Judah, each
        to his city, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'the ones who came with Zerubbabel, Jeshua, Nehemiah, Azariah, Raamiah,
        Nahamani, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum, and Baanah.  The men
        of the people of Israel numbered: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'the sons of Parosh, 2,172; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'the sons of Shephatiah, 372; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the sons of Arah, 652; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the sons of Pahath-moab of the sons of Jeshua and Joab, 2,818; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the sons of Elam, 1,254; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the sons of Zattu, 845; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the sons of Zaccai, 760; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the sons of Binnui, 648; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the sons of Bebai, 628; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the sons of Azgad, 2,322; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the sons of Adonikam, 667; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the sons of Bigvai, 2,067; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the sons of Adin, 655; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'the sons of Ater, of Hezekiah, 98; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'the sons of Hashum, 328; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'the sons of Bezai, 324; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'the sons of Hariph, 112; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'the sons of Gibeon, 95; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'the men of Bethlehem and Netophah, 188; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'the men of Anathoth, 128; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'the men of Beth-azmaveth, 42; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'the men of Kiriath-jearim, Chephirah and Beeroth, 743; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'the men of Ramah and Geba, 621; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'the men of Michmas, 122; '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'the men of Bethel and Ai, 123; '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'the men of the other Nebo, 52; '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'the sons of the other Elam, 1,254; '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'the sons of Harim, 320; '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'the sons of Jericho, 345; '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'the sons of Lod, Hadid and Ono, 721; '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'the sons of Senaah, 3,930.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '  These are the priests: the sons of Jedaiah of the house of Jeshua,
        973; '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'the sons of Immer, 1,052; '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'the sons of Pashhur, 1,247; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'the sons of Harim, 1,017.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '  These are the Levites: the sons of Jeshua, of Kadmiel, of the sons
        of Hodevah, 74. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'The singers: the sons of Asaph, 148. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'The gatekeepers: the sons of Shallum, the sons of Ater, the sons
        of Talmon, the sons of Akkub, the sons of Hatita, and the sons of Shobai,
        138.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'The temple servants: the sons of Ziha, the sons of Hasupha, the sons
        of Tabbaoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'the sons of Keros, the sons of Sia, the sons of Padon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'the sons of Lebana, the sons of Hagaba, the sons of Shalmai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'the sons of Hanan, the sons of Giddel, the sons of Gahar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'the sons of Reaiah, the sons of Rezin, the sons of Nekoda, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'the sons of Gazzam, the sons of Uzza, the sons of Paseah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'the sons of Besai, the sons of Meunim, the sons of Nephushesim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'the sons of Bakbuk, the sons of Hakupha, the sons of Harhur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'the sons of Bazlith, the sons of Mehida, the sons of Harsha, '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'the sons of Barkos, the sons of Sisera, the sons of Temah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'the sons of Neziah, the sons of Hatipha.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "The sons of Solomon\u2019s servants: the sons of Sotai, the sons
        of Sophereth, the sons of Perida, "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'the sons of Jaala, the sons of Darkon, the sons of Giddel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'the sons of Shephatiah, the sons of Hattil, the sons of Pochereth-hazzebaim,
        the sons of Amon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "All the temple servants and the sons of Solomon\u2019s servants,
        totaled 392.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "And these were the ones who came up from Tel-melah, Tel-harsha, Cherub,
        Addon and Immer; but they [had no birth records and] could not prove their
        fathers\u2019 houses or their descent, whether they were of Israel: "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'the sons of Delaiah, the sons of Tobiah, the sons of Nekoda, 642. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'Of the priests: the sons of Hobaiah, the sons of Hakkoz, and the
        sons of Barzillai, who [was so named because he had] married one of the daughters
        of Barzillai, the [well-known] Gileadite, and was named after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'These men searched for their ancestral registration among those recorded
        in the genealogies, but it was not located; so they were excluded from the
        priesthood as [ceremonially] unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: Total of People and Gifts'
      title: Total of People and Gifts
      number: 65
      content: "The governor told them that they should not eat any of the most holy
        food until a priest arose with Urim and Thummim [to determine God\u2019s
        will in the matter].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'The entire assembly together was 42,360, '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: 'besides their male and their female servants, of whom there were
        7,337; and they had 245 male and female singers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: 'Their horses were 736; their mules, 245; '
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: 'their camels, 435; their donkeys, 6,720.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: "Some from among the heads of fathers\u2019 households gave to the
        work. The governor gave to the treasury 1,000 gold drachmas, 50 basins, 530
        priests\u2019 garments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: "Some of the heads of fathers\u2019 households gave to the treasury
        for the work 20,000 gold drachmas and 2,200 silver minas. "
      comments: []
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: "And what the rest of the people gave was 20,000 gold drachmas, 2,000
        silver minas, and 67 priests\u2019 garments.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '73: '
      title: 
      number: 73
      content: So the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, some of
        the people, the temple servants, along with all Israel, lived in their cities. 
        And when the seventh month came, the sons (descendants) of Israel (Jacob)
        were in their cities.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ezra Reads the Law'
      title: Ezra Reads the Law
      number: 1
      content: '  Then all the people gathered together as one man at the open square
        in front of the Water Gate; and they asked Ezra the scribe to bring the Book
        of the Law of Moses which the Lord had given to Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Ezra the priest brought the Law before the assembly of men, women
        and all who could listen with understanding, on the first day of the seventh
        month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then he read from it, in front of the open square which was in front
        of the Water Gate, from early morning until midday, in the presence of the
        men and women, those who could understand; and all the people listened carefully
        to the Book of the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Ezra the scribe stood on a [large] wooden platform which they had
        constructed for this purpose. And beside him [on the platform] stood Mattithiah,
        Shema, Anaiah, Uriah, Hilkiah, and Maaseiah on his right; and Pedaiah, Mishael,
        Malchijah, Hashum, Hashbaddanah, Zechariah, and Meshullam on his left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ezra opened the book in the sight of all the people, for he was standing
        above them; and when he opened it, all the people stood up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Ezra blessed the Lord, the great God. And all the people answered,
        \u201CAmen, Amen!\u201D while lifting up their hands; and they knelt down
        and worshiped the Lord with their faces toward the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Also Jeshua, Bani, Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodiah, Maaseiah,
        Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, Pelaiah, and the Levites, explained the
        Law to the people, and the people remained in their places. '
      comments: []
    - name: "8: \u201CThis Day Is Holy\u201D"
      title: "\u201CThis Day Is Holy\u201D"
      number: 8
      content: 'So they read from the Book of the Law of God, translating and explaining
        it so that the people understood the reading.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Nehemiah, who was the governor, and Ezra the priest and scribe,
        and the Levites who taught the people said to all the people, \u201CThis
        day is holy to the Lord your God; do not mourn or weep.\u201D For all the
        people were weeping when they heard the words of the Law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Ezra said to them, \u201CGo [your way], eat the rich festival
        food, drink the sweet drink, and send portions to him for whom nothing is
        prepared; for this day is holy to our Lord. And do not be worried, for the
        joy of the Lord is your strength and your stronghold.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the Levites quieted all the people, saying, \u201CBe still, for
        the day is holy; do not be worried.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Feast of Booths Restored'
      title: Feast of Booths Restored
      number: 12
      content: 'Then all the people went on their way to eat, to drink, to send portions
        [of food to others] and to celebrate a great festival, because they understood
        the words which had been communicated to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "On the second day, all of the heads of fathers\u2019 households of
        all the people, the priests, and the Levites, were gathered before Ezra the
        scribe to gain insight into the words of the Law (divine instruction). "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They found written in the Law how the Lord had commanded through
        Moses that the Israelites should live in booths (huts) during the feast of
        the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So they proclaimed and published an announcement in all their cities
        and in Jerusalem, saying, \u201CGo out to the hills and bring olive branches,
        wild olive, myrtle, palm, and other leafy branches to make booths, as it
        is written.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So the people went out and brought them and made booths for themselves,
        each on the roof of his house, and in their courtyards and the courtyards
        of God\u2019s house, and in the open square of the Water Gate and in the
        square of the Gate of Ephraim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The entire assembly of those who had returned from the captivity
        made booths and lived in them. Indeed since the days of Joshua the son of
        Nun until that very day, the Israelites had not done so. And there was great
        rejoicing and celebration. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Every day, from the first day to the last, Ezra read from the Book
        of the Law of God. They celebrated the feast for seven days; on the eighth
        day there was a [closing] solemn assembly in accordance with the ordinance.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The People Confess Their Sin'
      title: The People Confess Their Sin
      number: 1
      content: '  Now on the twenty-fourth day of this month the Israelites assembled
        with fasting and in sackcloth and with dirt on their heads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The descendants of Israel (Jacob) separated themselves from all foreigners,
        and stood and confessed their sins and the wrongdoings of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'While they stood in their places, they read from the Book of the
        Law of the Lord their God for a fourth of the day and for another fourth
        [of it] they confessed [their sins] and worshiped the Lord their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On the platform of the Levites stood Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah,
        Bunni, Sherebiah, Bani, and Chenani, and they called out with a loud voice
        to the Lord their God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the Levites\u2014Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabneiah, Sherebiah,
        Hodiah, Shebaniah, and Pethahiah\u2014said, \u201CStand up and bless (praise,
        honor) the Lord your God from everlasting to everlasting.May Your glorious
        name be blessedAnd exalted above all blessing and praise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "[And Ezra said],\u201CYou are the Lord, You alone;You have made the
        heavens,The heaven of heavens with all their host (the heavenly bodies),The
        earth and everything that is on it,The seas and everything that is in them.You
        give life to all of them,And the heavenly host is bowing down [in worship]
        to You.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You are the Lord God,Who chose AbramAnd brought him out of Ur of
        the Chaldees,And gave him the name Abraham.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You found his heart to be faithful before You,And You made a covenant
        with himTo give him the land of the Canaanite,Of the Hittite, of the Amorite,Of
        the Perizzite, the Jebusite, and the Girgashite\u2014To give it to his descendants.And
        You have fulfilled Your promise,For You are righteous and just.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYou saw our fathers\u2019 affliction in Egypt,And You heard
        their cry by the Red Sea (Sea of Reeds).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then You performed signs and wonders against Pharaoh,Against all
        his servants and all the people of his land;For You knew that they behaved
        arrogantly toward them (the Israelites),And You made a name for Yourself,
        as it is to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You divided the sea before them,So that they passed through the midst
        of the sea on dry land;You hurled their pursuers into the depths,Like a stone
        into mighty and raging waters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And with a pillar of cloud You led them by day,And with a pillar
        of fire by nightTo light the way for themIn which they were to go.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then You came down on Mount Sinai,And spoke with them from heaven;And
        You gave them fair ordinances and true laws,Good statutes and commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So You made known to them Your holy Sabbath,And gave them commandments,
        statutes, and law,  Through Your servant Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You gave them bread from heaven for their hunger,And brought water
        for them out of a rock for their thirst,And You told them to enter and take
        possession ofThe land that You swore to give them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBut they, our fathers, acted arrogantly;They stiffened their
        necks and would not heed Your commandments.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They refused to listen and obey,And did not remember Your wondrous
        acts which You had performed among them;So they stiffened their necks and
        [in their rebellion] appointed a leader in order to return them to slavery
        in Egypt.But You are a God of forgiveness,Gracious and merciful and compassionate, 
        Slow to anger and abounding in lovingkindness;And You did not abandon them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Even when they had made for themselvesA calf of cast metalAnd said,
        \u2018This is your godWho brought you up from Egypt,\u2019And committed great
        [and contemptible] blasphemies,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You, in Your great mercy and compassion,Did not abandon them in the
        wilderness;The pillar of the cloud did not leave them by day,To lead them
        in the way,Nor the pillar of fire by night, to light for them the way they
        should go.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You [also] gave Your good Spirit to instruct them,You did not withhold
        Your manna from their mouth,And You gave them water for their thirst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Indeed, for forty years You sustained them in the wilderness; they
        lacked nothing,Their clothes did not wear out, and their feet did not swell.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You also gave them kingdoms and peoples,And You allotted the kingdoms
        to them as a boundary.So they took possession of the land of Sihon king of
        HeshbonAnd the land of Og king of Bashan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You made their children as numerous as the stars of heaven,And You
        brought them into the landWhich You told their fathers to enter and possess.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So their sons (descendants) went in and took possession of the land;And
        You subdued before them the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites,And You
        gave them into their hand, with their kings and the peoples of the land,To
        do with them as they pleased.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'They captured fortified cities and a fertile land.They took possession
        of houses full of all good things,Hewn cisterns, vineyards, olive groves,And
        fruit trees in abundance.So they ate and were filled and became fat,And they
        reveled and were delighted in Your great goodness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CYet they were disobedient and rebelled against You,And cast
        Your law behind their backsAnd killed Your prophets who warned themTo return
        to You;And they committed great [and contemptible] blasphemies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Therefore You handed them over to their enemies who oppressed them. 
        But when they cried out to You in the time of their suffering and distress,You
        heard them from heaven, and according to Your great compassion You gave them
        people to rescue them.Who rescued them from the hand of their enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But as soon as they had rest, they again did evil before You;Therefore
        You abandoned them into the hand of their enemies, so that they ruled over
        them.Yet when they turned and cried out again to You, You heard them from
        heaven,And You rescued them many times in accordance with Your compassion,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And You admonished them and warned them to turn them back to Your
        law.Yet they acted presumptuously and arrogantly and did not heed Your commandments,
        but sinned against Your ordinances,Which by keeping, a man will live.But
        they turned a stubborn shoulder, stiffened their neck, and would not listen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Yet You were patient with them for many years,And admonished them
        and warned them by Your Spirit through Your prophets;Still they would not
        listen.Therefore You gave them into the hand (power) of the peoples of the
        lands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Yet in Your great compassion You did not utterly destroy them or
        abandon them,For You are a gracious and merciful God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, our God, the great, the mighty, and the awesome
        God, who keeps the covenant and lovingkindness,Do not let all the hardship
        seem insignificant before You,Which has come upon us, our kings, our princes,
        our priests, our prophets, our fathers and on all Your people,Since the time
        of the kings of Assyria to this day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'However, You are just and righteous in everything that has come upon
        us;For You have dealt faithfully, but we have acted wickedly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Our kings, our princes, our priests, and our fathers have not kept
        Your lawOr paid attention to Your commandments and Your warnings which You
        have given them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'But they, in their kingdom,With Your great goodness which You gave
        them,With the broad and rich land which You set before them,Did not serve
        You or turn from their wicked deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Behold, we are slaves today,And as for the land which You gave our
        fathers, to eat of its fruit and its goodness,Behold, we are slaves in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: A Covenant Results'
      title: A Covenant Results
      number: 37
      content: 'Its abundant produce is for the kingsWhom You have set over us because
        of our sins;They also rule over our bodiesAnd over our cattle as they please,So
        we are in great distress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CNow because of all thisWe are making an agreement in writing;And
        on the sealed document are the names of our princes, our Levites, and our
        priests.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Signers of the Document'
      title: Signers of the Document
      number: 1
      content: '    Now these were the names on the sealed document: Nehemiah the
        governor, the son of Hacaliah. And Zedekiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Pashhur, Amariah, Malchijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Maaziah, Bilgai, Shemaiah\u2014these were the priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the Levites: Jeshua the son of Azaniah, Binnui of the sons of
        Henadad, Kadmiel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and their brothers: Shebaniah, Hodiah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Mica, Rehob, Hashabiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hodiah, Bani, Beninu. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The leaders of the people: Parosh, Pahath-moab, Elam, Zattu, Bani, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Bunni, Azgad, Bebai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Adonijah, Bigvai, Adin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Hodiah, Hashum, Bezai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hariph, Anathoth, Nebai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Meshezabel, Zadok, Jaddua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Hoshea, Hananiah, Hasshub, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Hallohesh, Pilha, Shobek, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Rehum, Hashabnah, Maaseiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Ahiah, Hanan, Anan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Obligations of the Document'
      title: Obligations of the Document
      number: 27
      content: 'Malluch, Harim, Baanah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now the rest of the people\u2014the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers,
        the singers, the temple servants, and all those who had separated themselves
        from the peoples of the lands to the Law of God, their wives, their sons,
        their daughters, all those who had knowledge and understanding\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "are joining with their fellow Israelites, their nobles, and are taking
        on themselves a curse and an oath to walk in God\u2019s Law, which was given
        through Moses the servant of God, and to keep and to observe all the commandments
        of God our Lord, and His ordinances and statutes: "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'and that we will not give our daughters [as wives] to the peoples
        of the land or take their daughters for our sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'As for the peoples of the land who bring merchandise or any grain
        on the Sabbath day to sell, we will not buy from them on the Sabbath or on
        a holy day; and we will give up raising crops during the seventh year [leaving
        the land uncultivated], and forgive every debt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Also we pledge ourselves to contribute yearly one third of a shekel
        for the service [expenses] of the house of our God: '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'for the showbread; for the continual grain offerings and the continual
        burnt offerings; [for the offerings on] the Sabbaths, the New Moons, the
        [feasts at] appointed times; for the holy things, for the sin offerings to
        make atonement for Israel; and for all the work of the house of our God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "We have also cast lots\u2014the priests, the Levites, and the people\u2014for
        [contributing] the supply of wood, to bring it to the house of our God, according
        to our fathers\u2019 households, at set times annually, to burn on the altar
        of the Lord our God, as it is written in the Law; "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'and [we obligate ourselves] to bring the first fruits of our ground
        and the first fruits of all the fruit of every tree to the house of the Lord
        annually, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'as well as the firstborn of our sons and of our cattle, as is written
        in the Law, and the firstborn of our herds and flocks, to bring to the house
        of our God, for the priests who minister in the house of our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'We will bring the first [and best] of our dough, our contributions,
        the fruit of every tree, the new wine and the [olive] oil to the priests,
        to the chambers of the house of our God, and the tithe of our ground to the
        Levites, for the Levites are the ones who receive the tithes in all the rural
        towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The priest, the son of Aaron, shall be with the Levites when they
        receive tithes, and they shall bring one-tenth of the tithes up to the house
        of our God, to the chambers of the storehouse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: For the Israelites and the sons of Levi shall bring the offering of
        the grain, the new wine, and the oil to the chambers; the utensils of the
        sanctuary, the priests who are ministering, the gatekeepers, and the singers
        are there. In this manner, we will not neglect the house of our God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Time Passes; Heads of Provinces'
      title: Time Passes; Heads of Provinces
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the leaders of the people lived in Jerusalem; but the rest
        of the people cast lots to bring one [person] out of ten to live in Jerusalem,
        the holy city, while nine-tenths remained in the other cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the people blessed all the men who volunteered to live in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "These are the heads of the provinces who lived in Jerusalem, but
        in the cities of Judah everyone lived on his property in their cities\u2014the
        Israelites, the priests, the Levites, the temple servants, and the descendants
        of Solomon\u2019s servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And some of the sons of Judah and some of the sons of Benjamin lived
        in Jerusalem. From the sons of Judah: Athaiah the son of Uzziah, the son
        of Zechariah, the son of Amariah, the son of Shephatiah, the son of Mahalalel,
        of the sons of Perez; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Maaseiah the son of Baruch, the son of Col-hozeh, the son of Hazaiah,
        the son of Adaiah, the son of Joiarib, the son of Zechariah, the son of the
        Shilonite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'All the sons of Perez who lived at Jerusalem were 468 able men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'These are the sons of Benjamin: Sallu the son of Meshullam, the son
        of Joed, the son of Pedaiah, the son of Kolaiah, the son of Maaseiah, the
        son of Ithiel, son of Jeshaiah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and after him Gabbai and Sallai, 928. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Joel the son of Zichri was their overseer, and Judah the son of Hassenuah
        was second in command of the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Of the priests: Jedaiah the son of Joiarib, Jachin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Seraiah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok,
        the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, the leader of the house of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and their brothers (relatives, fellow workers) who did the work of
        the house, 822; and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pelaliah, the son
        of Amzi, the son of Zechariah, the son of Pashhur, the son of Malchijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and his brothers, heads of fathers\u2019 households, 242; and Amashsai
        the son of Azarel, the son of Ahzai, the son of Meshillemoth, the son of
        Immer, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and their brothers, brave men, 128. Their overseer was Zabdiel the
        son of Haggedolim [one of the great men].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now from the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam,
        the son of Hashabiah, the son of Bunni; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and Shabbethai and Jozabad, from the leaders of the Levites, who
        were in charge of the outside work of the house of God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Mattaniah the son of Mica, the son of Zabdi, the son of Asaph, who
        was the leader to begin the thanksgiving in prayer, and Bakbukiah, second
        among his brothers; and Abda the son of Shammua, the son of Galal, the son
        of Jeduthun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'All the Levites in the holy city totaled 284.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Outside Jerusalem'
      title: Outside Jerusalem
      number: 19
      content: 'The gatekeepers: Akkub, Talmon, and their kinsmen, who kept watch
        at the gates, totaled 172.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now the rest of Israel, the priests and the Levites, were in all
        the cities of Judah, each on his own inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But the temple servants were living in Ophel; Ziha and Gishpa were
        in charge of the temple servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The overseer of the Levites in Jerusalem was Uzzi the son of Bani,
        the son of Hashabiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Mica, from Asaph\u2019s
        sons, who were the singers in regard to the work of the house of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For there was a command from the [Persian] king regarding the singers,
        as to their daily task. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Pethahiah the son of Meshezabel, of the sons of Zerah the son of
        Judah, was the king\u2019s representative in all matters concerning the people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'As for the villages with their fields, some sons (descendants) of
        Judah lived in Kiriath-arba and its towns, Dibon and its towns, and Jekabzeel
        and its villages, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'in Jeshua, in Moladah, in Beth-pelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'in Hazar-shual and in Beersheba and its towns, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'in Ziklag and in Meconah and its towns, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'in En-rimmon, in Zorah, and in Jarmuth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Zanoah, Adullam, and their villages, Lachish and its fields, and
        Azekah and its towns. So they camped from Beersheba as far as the Hinnom
        Valley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The sons (descendants) of Benjamin also lived from Geba onward, at
        Michmash, Aija, Bethel and its towns, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'at Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Hazor, Ramah, Gittaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Lod, and Ono, the Valley of the Craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: And certain divisions of the Levites in Judah belonged to Benjamin.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Priests and Levites who Returned to Jerusalem with Zerubbabel'
      title: Priests and Levites who Returned to Jerusalem with Zerubbabel
      number: 1
      content: '  Now these are the priests and Levites who came up with Zerubbabel
        the son of Shealtiel and with Jeshua: Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Amariah, Malluch, Hattush, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Shecaniah, Rehum, Meremoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Iddo, Ginnethoi, Abijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Mijamin, Maadiah, Bilgah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Shemaiah, Joiarib, Jedaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, and Jedaiah. These were the heads of the priests
        and their kinsman in the days of Jeshua.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Levites were Jeshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah, and Mattaniah
        who was in charge of the songs of thanksgiving and praise, he and his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Also Bakbukiah and Unni, their brothers, stood opposite them in their
        divisions of service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Jeshua became the father of Joiakim, Joiakim of Eliashib, Eliashib
        of Joiada, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and Joiada became the father of Jonathan, and Jonathan of Jaddua.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And in the days of Joiakim, the priests, the heads of fathers\u2019
        households were: of Seraiah, Meraiah; of Jeremiah, Hananiah; "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'of Ezra, Meshullam; of Amariah, Jehohanan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'of Malluchi, Jonathan; of Shebaniah, Joseph; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'of Harim, Adna; of Meraioth, Helkai; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'of Iddo, Zechariah; of Ginnethon, Meshullam; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'of Abijah, Zichri; of Miniamin and of Moadiah, Piltai; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'of Bilgah, Shammua; of Shemaiah, Jehonathan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'of Joiarib, Mattenai; of Jedaiah, Uzzi; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'of Sallai, Kallai; of Amok, Eber; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Chief Levites'
      title: The Chief Levites
      number: 21
      content: 'of Hilkiah, Hashabiah; of Jedaiah, Nethanel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "As for the Levites in the days of Eliashib, Joiada, Johanan, and
        Jaddua, the heads of fathers\u2019 households were registered; so were the
        priests, during the reign of Darius the Persian. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The sons of Levi, heads of fathers\u2019 households, were recorded
        in the Book of the Chronicles until the days of Johanan the son of Eliashib. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The heads of the Levites were Hashabiah, Sherebiah, and Jeshua the
        son of Kadmiel, and their brothers opposite them, to praise and to give thanks,
        as commanded by David the man of God, [one] division [singing] in response
        to [the men in the opposite] division. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Mattaniah, Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon, and Akkub were
        gatekeepers keeping watch at the storehouses of the gates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Dedication of the Wall'
      title: Dedication of the Wall
      number: 26
      content: 'These men served in the days of Joiakim the son of Jeshua, the son
        of Jozadak, and in the days of Nehemiah the governor and Ezra the priest
        and scribe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought out the
        Levites from all their places in order to bring them to Jerusalem to celebrate
        the dedication with gladness, with hymns of thanksgiving, and with songs
        to the accompaniment of cymbals, harps, and lyres. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So the sons of the singers gathered together from the district around
        Jerusalem, and from the villages of the Netophathites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'from Beth-gilgal and from the fields of Geba and Azmaveth, for the
        singers had built villages for themselves around Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Procedures for the Temple'
      title: Procedures for the Temple
      number: 30
      content: 'The priests and the Levites purified themselves; they also purified
        the people, the gates, and the wall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then I had the leaders of Judah come up on the wall, and I appointed
        two large thanksgiving choirs, the first one proceeding to the right on top
        of the wall toward the Refuse Gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Hoshaiah and half of the leaders of Judah followed them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'with Azariah, Ezra, Meshullam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Judah, Benjamin, Shemaiah, and Jeremiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "and some of the priests\u2019 sons with trumpets, and Zechariah the
        son of Jonathan, the son of Shemaiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Micaiah,
        the son of Zaccur, the son of Asaph, "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and his brothers, Shemaiah, Azarel, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethanel,
        Judah, and Hanani, with the musical instruments of David the man of God.
        And Ezra the scribe went in front of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "At the Fountain Gate they went directly up the steps of the City
        of David by the stairway of the wall above David\u2019s house to the Water
        Gate on the east.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The second choir went to the left; I followed with half of the people
        on the wall, above the Tower of the Furnaces, to the Broad Wall, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and above the Gate of Ephraim, and by the Old Gate, by the Fish Gate,
        by the Tower of Hananel and the Tower of the Hundred, as far as the Sheep
        Gate; and they stopped at the Gate of the Guard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Then the two choirs stood in the house of God. So did I, and half
        of the officials with me; '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'and the priests Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Micaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah
        and Hananiah, with trumpets; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'and Maaseiah, Shemaiah, Eleazar, Uzzi, Jehohanan, Malchijah, Elam,
        and Ezer. And the singers sang, with Jezrahiah as their leader. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Also on that day they offered great sacrifices and rejoiced because
        God had given them great joy; the women and children also rejoiced, so that
        the joy of Jerusalem was heard from far away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'On that day men were appointed over the chambers for the stores,
        the contributions, the first fruits, and the tithes, to gather into them
        from the fields of the cities the portions required by the law for the priests
        and the Levites; for Judah rejoiced over the priests and Levites who served. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And they performed the worship of their God and the service of purification;
        so did the singers and gatekeepers, as David and his son Solomon had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'For in the days of David and Asaph, in ancient times, there were
        leaders of singers, songs of praise and hymns of thanksgiving to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: So in the days of Zerubbabel and [later of] Nehemiah, all Israel would
        give the daily portions for the singers and the gatekeepers; and they set
        apart the consecrated portion for the Levites, and the Levites set apart
        the consecrated portion for the sons of Aaron [the priests].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Foreigners Excluded'
      title: Foreigners Excluded
      number: 1
      content: '  On that day they read aloud from the book of Moses so that the
        people could hear [its words], and in it was found written that no Ammonite
        or Moabite could ever enter the assembly of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'because they did not meet the Israelites with bread and water, but
        hired Balaam against them to curse them. Yet our God turned the curse into
        a blessing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Tobiah Expelled and the Temple Cleansed'
      title: Tobiah Expelled and the Temple Cleansed
      number: 3
      content: 'When the Jews heard the law, they separated from Israel all who were
        of foreign descent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now prior to this, Eliashib the priest, who was appointed over the
        chambers of the house of our God, and was related to Tobiah [our adversary], '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'had prepared for Tobiah a large room (chamber) where previously they
        had put the grain offerings, the frankincense, the utensils, and the tithes
        of grain, new wine, and [olive] oil which were given by commandment for the
        Levites, the singers, and gatekeepers, and the contributions for the priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But during all this time I was not at Jerusalem, for in the thirty-second
        year of Artaxerxes [Persian] king of Babylon I went to the king. Then after
        some time I asked for a leave [of absence] from the king, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and I came to Jerusalem. Then I discovered the evil [thing] that
        Eliashib had done for Tobiah by preparing a room for him in the courtyards
        of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "It was very displeasing to me, so I threw all of Tobiah\u2019s household
        furnishings out of the room. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Tithes Restored'
      title: Tithes Restored
      number: 9
      content: 'Then I gave an order, and they cleaned the rooms; and I put back
        there the utensils of the house of God with the grain offerings and the frankincense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I also discovered that the portions due the Levites had not been
        given to them, so that the Levites and the singers who did the work had gone
        away, each one back to his own field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then I reprimanded the officials and said, \u201CWhy is the house
        of God neglected?\u201D So I gathered the Levites and singers together and
        restored them at their posts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then all Judah brought the tithe of the grain, the new wine, and
        the oil to the storehouses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I appointed [as treasurers] over the storehouses: Shelemiah the priest,
        Zadok the scribe, and Pedaiah of the Levites; assisting them was Hanan son
        of Zaccur, the son of Mattaniah; for they were considered faithful and reliable,
        and their task was to distribute [supplies] to their brothers (fellow Levites). '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Sabbath Restored'
      title: Sabbath Restored
      number: 14
      content: 'O my God, remember me concerning this and do not wipe out my loyal
        deeds and kindnesses which I have done for the house of my God and for its
        services.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In those days I saw some in Judah who were treading wine presses
        on the Sabbath, and bringing in sheaves or sacks of grain and loading them
        on donkeys, as well as wine, grapes, figs, and all kinds of loads, which
        they brought into Jerusalem on the Sabbath day. So I protested and warned
        them on the day they sold the produce. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Also men of Tyre were living there who brought fish and all kinds
        of merchandise, and they were selling them to the people of Judah on the
        Sabbath, even in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then I reprimanded the nobles of Judah, and said to them, \u201CWhat
        is this evil thing that you are doing\u2014profaning the Sabbath day? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Did your fathers (ancestors) not do the same, and did our God not
        bring all this trouble on us and on this city? Yet you are adding to the
        wrath on Israel by profaning the Sabbath.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now when it began to get dark at the gates of Jerusalem before the
        Sabbath [began], I commanded that the doors be shut and not be opened until
        after the Sabbath. Then I stationed some of my servants at the gates so that
        no load [of merchandise] would enter [Jerusalem] on the Sabbath day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So once or twice the merchants and sellers of every kind of merchandise
        spent the night outside Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But I warned them, saying, \u201CWhy do you spend the night by the
        wall? If you do so again, I will use force against you.\u201D From that time
        on, they did not come on the Sabbath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Mixed Marriages Forbidden'
      title: Mixed Marriages Forbidden
      number: 22
      content: 'And I commanded the Levites to purify themselves and come and guard
        the gates to keep the Sabbath day holy. O my God, remember me concerning
        this also and have compassion on me according to the greatness of Your lovingkindness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In those days I also saw Jews who had married women from Ashdod,
        Ammon, and Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'As for their children, half spoke in the language of Ashdod, and
        none of them knew how to speak [Hebrew] the language of Judah, but only the
        language of his own people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So I contended with them and cursed them and struck some of them
        and pulled out their hair, and made them swear by God, saying, \u201CYou
        shall not give your daughters [in marriage] to their sons, nor take [any
        of] their daughters for your sons or for yourselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Did not Solomon king of Israel sin [greatly against God] regarding
        these things? Yet among the many nations there was no king like him. He was
        loved by his God, and God made him king over all Israel; nevertheless the
        foreign women caused even him to sin [by turning to other gods and so, judged
        by God, he lost his kingdom]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Do we then hear about you that you have done all this great evil,
        acting unfaithfully against our God by marrying foreign (pagan) women?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'One of the sons of Joiada, the son of Eliashib the high priest, was
        a son-in-law of Sanballat the Horonite, so I chased him away from me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'O my God, remember them, because they have defiled the priesthood
        and the covenant of the priesthood and the Levites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Thus I cleansed and purified them from everything foreign (pagan),
        and I defined the duties of the priests and Levites, each one in his task; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: and I provided for the wood offering at appointed times and for the
        first fruits. O my God, [please] remember me for good [and imprint me on
        Your heart].
      comments: []
